          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1648553939682-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>cannellini beans</strong>, <strong>chopped rosemary</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min until fragrant, then add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>creamy stock </strong>to the pan with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-6 min or until the vegetables are tender and the stock has thickened to a stew-like consistency – this is your <strong>herby cannellini bean stew</strong></p>",
